Savory Lentil and Quinoa Protein Pancakes

1 c red lentils
1 c white quinoa
1 1/4 c water
1 garlic clove, minced
1/4 c fresh cilantro leaves
1 tbsp coconut oil
1 tbsp fresh lemon juice
1 tbsp apple cider vinegar
3/4 tsp baking powder
1/2 tsp garlic powder
1/2 tsp coriander
1-1 1/2 tsp large grain sea salt or to taste
black pepper to taste
1 serrano pepper, deseeded, deveined, and minced
3 tbsp minced shallots

Add the lentils and quinoa o 2 separate airtight containers. Pour water into both containers until it completely covers (even 2" extra is good). Refrigerate both overnight or for at least 8hrs. Drain and thoroughly rinse both. Add both to a food processor along with 1 1/4 c water, minced garlic, cilantro leaves, coconut oil, lemon juice, vinegar, baking powder, garlic powder, coriander, salt, and pepper. Process for 2-3 min or until the batter is completely smooth. Transfer the batter to a large mixing bowl and gently fold in the peppers and shallots. Heat a medium skillet or griddle pan over medium heat. Spray or rub the pan with coconut oil. Once the pan is hot, drop a full ladle of batter on it and cook for 2-2 1/2 min per side.You want the pancake to just turn golden in color. Makes 4 large or 5-6 medium pancakes.

Topping suggestions:
sliced avocado
greens
